items.title: Wall Street ends sharply higher with assist from tech; investors eye Trump policies
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 339.86 points, or 0.80%, to 42,732.13, the S&P 500 gained 73.92 points, or 1.26%, to 5,942.47 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 340.88 points, or 1.77%, to 19,621.68.

items.title: HDFC Bank gets RBI nod to purchase 9.5% stake in AU Small Finance Bank
items.description: HDFC Bank also disclosed it has also secured RBI’s nod to acquire up to a 9.5 percent aggregate stake in Kotak Mahindra Bank and Capital Small Finance Bank

items.title: Market extend gains in second week; rupee depreciate
items.description: The rupee depreciation continued in this week also as the currency ended 24 paise lower at 85.78 per dollar on January 3 against the December 27 closing of 85.54.

items.title: Vedanta's Q3 aluminium output rises 3%, achieves record mined metal production
items.description: Meanwhile, oil and gas production dropped 19 percent year-on-year to 9.1 million barrels of oil equivalent per day.

items.title: These 50 smallcaps gain between 10-40% as broader indices outperform
items.description: This week, BSE Sensex rose 524.04 points or 0.66 percent to close at 79,223.11, while the Nifty50 index added 191.35 points or 0.80 percent to finish at 24,004.75. However, BSE Large-cap, Mid-cap and Small-cap indices rose 1 percent, 1.3 percent and 2 percent.

items.title: Bajaj Finance Q3 biz update: AUM rises 28%, records highest-ever quarterly customer additions
items.description: The NBFC also reported its highest-ever quarterly new loans booked at 12.06 million in Q3 FY25, marking a 22 percent growth from 9.86 million in the same quarter last year.
